column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

There were 275 export and 75 young cattle penned representing an increase of 120 head week-on-week. There was one order absent from the regular buying group who were more selective in a cheaper market. Quality declined with secondary and plainer cattle throughout. The young cattle lacked finish and sold mostly to restockers. Grown cattle sold up to 40c/kg cheaper with quality an issue. Cows gave back 15c to 30c/kg. Heavy bulls eased 4c/kg. 

Young steers to restockers sold from 240c to 310c/kg. Heifers to restockers made between 190c and 291c/kg. Manufacturing steers sold between 266c and 308c/kg. Most light and medium weight cows made from 212c to 266c/kg. Heavy weight cows sold mostly from 230c to 310c/kg. Heavy bulls made between 290c and 332c/kg. 

Market reporter: Brendan Fletcher.
